The last time I saw Twitch was when he guest judged Freestyle Roulette for @galenhooks . I wasn’t even sure that he would remember me from our brief interactions over the years, but he greeted me like an old friend and even complimented my team @vibrvncy for how we were moving around and capturing the battles.

The warm energy of his presence was palpable, and undoubtedly appreciated by everyone in attendance - especially the dancers competing that night. His excitement and enthusiasm watching the dancers was inspiring to witness. Despite everything he had “moved up” to and gone on to achieve, there was clearly still a brilliant passion for the art form and community that he came from.

Sending love to his family, and everyone hurting from this massive loss.

Rest in Power, Boss 🕊️🤍 @sir_twitch_alot

I still don’t quite know what to say, and there’s a lot I’m still processing about the closure of @sinostage.

Maybe I speak better though images than through words, so here are just a few of my cherished memories dating back to 2015.

For many of us, China was a very foreign place, but Sinostage always felt like home. They took on the responsibility of bridging the gap between China and the global dance community with the utmost care, and worked tirelessly to develop the local scene, fostering talent and providing a vast array of opportunities and experiences for their dancers, staff, and students.

I’m fortunate to have had so many unforgettable life experiences and professional achievements by way of Sinostage, but more than that, I found the greatest of friends in Koko and Eli, who believed in and supported me and my @kinjaz @vibrvncy family from day 1. Thank you for inviting and entrusting me to play a small part in the Sinostage story.

We created some amazing things together, from the physical spaces of @kinjazdojochina to the international celebration known as @arenadancecomp . In due time, I hope that you will look back on everything with pride and the fondest of memories.

To all of my #sinostage fam, this may be the end of a chapter, but I believe that the journey is far from over. 

Love you all 🤍
#sinostageforever

Memory fragments from the most epic launch event.

remember me? i’m 32 now. 🫠

2023 feels like we’re lost in the digital labyrinth, where layoffs are rampant and AI reigns supreme. feeling overwhelmed, overstimulated, and struggling to keep up with all the different versions of her.

as a creator and someone who works in tech — it’s simultaneously exhilarating and exhausting. our human minds aren’t evolving fast enough for this explosion of data.

social media is a double edge sword, and as someone who had (at one point) tied too much of my personal worth to my online persona … i’ve finally given my permission to touch some f*ckn grass and discover myself again beyond the digital realm. (journal. meditate. sleep. exercise. have become my allies) — i highly recommend it if you can relate to this.

just a gentle reminder to step away from the virtual noise every now and then — rejuvinate the mind, nurture your creativity and engage with the world in a more profound level. online and offline. 🤍🫶

At the tail end of 2023, I directed the “GOAT” Dance MV for @number_i_staff , alongside @riehata as choreographer and my @vibrvncy brother @geraldnonadoez as DP. 

For this iteration of their debut single launch, we wanted to highlight their Japanese culture, and juxtapose the aesthetic of traditional architecture with contemporary color and lighting.

The shoot was a phenomenal effort made possible an outstanding crew within a very short amount of time. Huge thank you to Rie and the Number_i team for bringing us out to Japan for this! 🙏💜
